The wise woman repeated the words again, "and Arthur Beeton."

Araphen looked at her, his eyes wet with tears. He then held out his hand to shake hers. A soft pat and a sigh later, they began to chat in a light manner. Araphen mentioned that he had gone on an expedition with his wife to a nearby volcanic island.

"It's quite a place, isn't it?"

"A shame I wasn't there with you, Granny. I would have loved to learn about lava."

